AWS API Gateway Learning
Introduction

This learning activity was performed to understand AWS API Gateway concepts, API communication workflows, API types, and serverless API architecture. The session included AWS documentation reading, video learning, and concept exploration to understand how frontend applications communicate with backend services using APIs.

The learning mainly focused on understanding REST API, HTTP API, WebSocket API, request-response workflows, API security, traffic management, monitoring concepts, and AWS API Gateway integration with backend services such as AWS Lambda.

Objective

The objectives of this learning session were:

To understand AWS API Gateway service and architecture.
To learn API communication and request-response workflows.
To understand REST API, HTTP API, and WebSocket API concepts.
To explore API Gateway integration with backend services.
To study API security, rate limiting, throttling, and monitoring concepts.
To improve understanding through AWS documentation and learning videos.
To strengthen cloud and serverless architecture concepts.
