API Communication Concepts Learned
What is an API

An API (Application Programming Interface) is a communication mechanism that allows applications and services to exchange data and functionality.

Examples:

Login APIs
Payment APIs
Product APIs
User profile APIs

Purpose:

To enable communication between frontend and backend systems.
What is API Gateway

AWS API Gateway is a managed AWS service used to create, manage, secure, monitor, and route APIs.

Purpose:

Request routing
API security
Monitoring
Traffic management
Backend integration
API Types Learned
1. REST API

REST API is a feature-rich API type used for enterprise and complex backend systems.

Features Studied
API Keys
Request Validation
Usage Plans
Advanced Security
Caching
Throttling
Concepts Learned
API Keys

Used to identify and control API usage.

Purpose:

Security
Usage tracking
Access control
Request Validation

Checks whether request data is valid before sending to backend services.

Purpose:

Prevent invalid requests
Improve backend security
Usage Plans

Controls API request limits for users.

Purpose:

Resource management
API monetization
Traffic control
Advanced Security

Supports:

IAM Authentication
OAuth
Cognito
Custom Authorizers

Purpose:

Enterprise-level API security
Caching

Stores frequently requested responses temporarily.

Purpose:

Faster response
Reduced backend load
Improved performance
Throttling

Controls request speed and traffic flow.

Purpose:

Prevent overload
Protect backend services
Purpose of REST API

Used for:

Enterprise systems
Banking applications
Large-scale backend architectures
Complex cloud systems
2. HTTP API

HTTP API is a lightweight and simplified API type mainly used for serverless and modern cloud applications.

Features Studied
Simple Routing
Lambda Integration
JWT Authentication
Lower Latency
Concepts Learned
Simple Routing

Routes requests to correct backend services.

Example:

/login → Login Service
/products → Product Service
Lambda Integration

HTTP APIs integrate efficiently with AWS Lambda.

Workflow:
User Request → HTTP API → Lambda → Response

Purpose:

Serverless architecture
JWT Authentication

JWT (JSON Web Token) is used for secure authentication and authorization.

Purpose:

User authentication
Secure API access
Lower Latency

HTTP APIs provide faster responses because of lightweight architecture.

Purpose:

Faster execution
Reduced cost
Improved performance
Purpose of HTTP API

Used for:

Serverless applications
Lightweight APIs
Lambda-based backend systems
Modern cloud-native applications
3. WebSocket API

WebSocket API supports real-time two-way communication between client and server.

Concepts Learned

Unlike REST and HTTP APIs:

WebSocket keeps connection continuously active.
Both client and server can send data anytime.

Purpose:

Real-time communication systems
Use Cases Studied
Chat applications
Live notifications
Online gaming
Real-time dashboards
Stock market applications
